{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Primary translator output is grammatically coherent and preserves source meaning, not just literal word substitution.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The failure boundary is model output quality (semantic adequacy/fluency), which cannot be reliably caught by pure logic tests or mocks. Even with correct wiring, real MT model behavior can fail this requirement, so LLM-DEP applies.","test_description":"Run the service against the real neural translation API on a fixed multilingual evaluation set; score meaning preservation and grammatical coherence with human-labeled or strong reference-based checks, and fail if quality thresholds regress.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"On translation API 503, service transparently falls back to dictionary translator and does not return an error.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The bug appears at module handoff (API client error -> fallback path -> response shaping). A unit test of one function can miss wiring/state propagation issues; real external infra is not required if 503 is simulated at the API boundary.","test_description":"Wire service + API adapter stub + real fallback translator (with test SQLite DB). Force API stub to return 503, assert caller receives successful fallback translation and no propagated error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Dictionary fallback returns correct stored translation for phrases present in SQLite.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Correctness depends on SQL/query/schema/data access behavior across modules and local DB I/O. Mocking DB can hide real lookup failures (collation, parameter binding, schema mismatch).","test_description":"Populate a real SQLite test DB with known phrase pairs, invoke fallback translator through its normal data-access layer, and assert exact expected translations for existing phrases.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Quality tracking computes character-level edit distance between primary and fallback outputs and stores the metric.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"While edit-distance math alone is unit-testable, this behavior includes persistence. Real failures often occur in compute-to-storage wiring (wrong field, dropped write, transactional bug), so module interaction is the minimum boundary.","test_description":"Execute translation flow with deterministic primary/fallback strings, verify computed edit distance value and confirm it is persisted in the expected record/table with correct association.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When both translators are available, service returns primary translation and logs quality comparison asynchronously in background.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is an orchestration/concurrency behavior across modules (primary selection + background metric logging). Failures are in async coordination and side effects, not in single-function logic; no real external API/model quality dependency is required.","test_description":"Run service with deterministic primary and fallback components enabled; assert response immediately uses primary output, then await/observe background job completion and verify quality log entry was written.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
